The Crisis of 2010‐11 
 
 
 
 
 
	  European countries have high debt relative to GDP; low growth 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 European Central Bank is not at the national level; does not necessarily back‐stop debt 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 Germans want to break the moral hazard regime; impose losses on creditors 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
  The IMF: always present at the destruction; continue incremental approach 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 Is austerity the answer; reluctance to restructure debts (unlike for emerging markets) 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
  Will Europe re‐affirm moral hazard (the “big bazooka”) or deal with the consequences of default? 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
  The Rise of China complete: Will the US dollar lose its reserve currency role? (Arvind Subramanian) 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

 
 
